@node edoc "Neutrix Documentation"

                             'Neutrix' 1.0

                          by Charles-N. Jacob

  'Neutrix' is a @{" Workbench game " link eplay} where the idea is to move down
coloured tiles that are located at the bottom of the game board, by
clicking on the arrows that are located under. When these tiles
disappear, all tiles located above will fall by one level. The
vacated uppermost position of that column will be replaced by a new
tile... or a neutral block, if there is one at the lowermost
position in that column.

  Avoid placing 2 coloured tiles or more of the same type next to
each other, either one beside another or one on top of another. If
that happens, these tiles will be 'neutrified', which means that
they will become neutral blocks. If an entire column contains only
neutral blocks, the game will be over.

  Have fun!

