@node eplay "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Neutrix" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed. However, the game requires a 68020(+)
Amiga with Workbench 2.0 or higher and a Workbench with at least
8 colours.

                             How to play?

  The game consists of an area filled with various coloured tiles,
on the lower row are a series of arrows that are pointing downward.
To play, click on one of these arrows, which will make the tile
located above that arrow to move down and disappear. Then, all
tiles located above in that column, will fall one level...

  The vacated uppermost position will be replaced by the 'Next' tile
which is displayed at the right of the game board... unless there
is a 'neutral block' located at the lowest position in the column.
In that case, the neutral block will go to the upper location of
the column...

  Each time a coloured tile disappears at the lowest part of a
column, you get 1 point. If several tiles of the same type are
consecutively removed, the number of points will increase to 2, 4,
8, 16 and so on...

  Avoid placing two tiles or more of the same pattern next to each
other (unless these are neutral blocks), on either sides and/or one
over another. If that happens, those tiles will be 'neutrified',
which means that the tiles will become neutral blocks... If an
entire column of tiles contains nothing but neutral blocks, the
game is over...

  Have fun!

  You can quit the game by clicking on the game window's close
button or by pressing on the 'Esc' key.

@endnode

